# OS X Server - Before You Start

# Hardware Recommendations
Due to their intended purpose, each OS X Server should have at least the following:

- 2.5GHz dual-core i5
- 500GB Hard Drive
- 8GB RAM
- 2 Network Connections
    - 1x Ethernet
    - 1x Thunderbolt Ethernet

## Firewall Requirements

In order to configure OS X Server and receive security-related updates, traffic to the following FQDNs over __TCP 443__ is necessary.
- swcdn.apple.com
- swdownload.apple.com
- swquery.apple.com
- swscan.apple.com

No other external-bound access is required.

Sources:  
https://support.apple.com/en-ca/HT202943